cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a model for sequence encoding in natural language processing tasks, which is a common topic in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The model uses self-attention networks, which are also commonly used in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the efficiency-memory trade-off, which is relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the model on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
